        Clause 287 [<span class="italic">Transfer of employees from OPRA to the Regulator</span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-04753'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_352' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        On Question, Whether Clause 287 shall stand part of the Bill?
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0665P0-04754'>
        <a name='S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_353'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-terence-higgins' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_353' title='Link to this speech by Mr Terence Higgins' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-terence-higgins" title="Mr Terence Higgins">Lord Higgins</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Why are we including subsection (2), which states:
            <q>The provisions of Regulation 7 of TUPE&#x2026;shall not apply to the transfer"?</q>
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0665P0-04755'>
        <a name='S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_354'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-patricia-hollis' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_354' title='Link to this speech by Ms Patricia Hollis' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-patricia-hollis" title="Ms Patricia Hollis">Baroness Hollis of Heigham</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Clause 287 makes specific provision in relation to staff who transfer from OPRA to the Pensions Regulator. It ensures that the terms and conditions of employment of staff who transfer will be protected, with the transfer expressly being made subject to the provisions of TUPE. However, those TUPE regulations do not protect occupational pension rights. Subsection (2) makes express provision for such rights to be protected. I commend the clause.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0665P0-04756'>
        <a name='S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_355'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-terence-higgins' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_355' title='Link to this speech by Mr Terence Higgins' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-terence-higgins" title="Mr Terence Higgins">Lord Higgins</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            If they are not normally protected. why are they being protected here?
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0665P0-04757'>
        <a name='S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_356'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-patricia-hollis' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_356' title='Link to this speech by Ms Patricia Hollis' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-patricia-hollis" title="Ms Patricia Hollis">Baroness Hollis of Heigham</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            We think it right to protect the occupational pension rights of staff who transfer from OPRA to the Pensions Regulator. TUPE does not provide for that, so we have to do it this way.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0665P0-04758'>
        <a name='S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_357'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-terence-higgins' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_357' title='Link to this speech by Mr Terence Higgins' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
