        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-patricia-hollis' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_393' title='Link to this speech by Ms Patricia Hollis' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-patricia-hollis" title="Ms Patricia Hollis">Baroness Hollis of Heigham</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            It is basically because the amendments that we originally envisaged were about the ring-fencing provisions, which have been superseded by the directive. The clause is about scheme rules. It is a little odd to be fished on amendments that are not on the Marshalled List; that is why I pushed the noble Lord on it.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0665P0-04795'>
        <a name='S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_394'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-roger-bootle-wilbraham' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_394' title='Link to this speech by Mr Roger Bootle-Wilbraham' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-roger-bootle-wilbraham" title="Mr Roger Bootle-Wilbraham">Lord Skelmersdale</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            They were on the Marshalled List.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0665P0-04796'>
        <a name='S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_395'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-patricia-hollis' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_395' title='Link to this speech by Ms Patricia Hollis' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
